<!DOCTYPE html>
<!--
  AIoTIE 2026 — Verify Portal Wrapper
  =====================================================================
  Tiny outer page whose ONLY job is to embed the standalone GAS verify
  portal inside an iframe with `allow="camera; microphone"` set on the
  iframe tag. That attribute is what tells the browser to forward
  camera permission down into the embedded GAS portal — without it,
  modern browsers strip getUserMedia at the iframe boundary and the
  live scanner inside the portal fails with "Permission denied".

  Why this is needed: Apps Script web apps serve their content
  inside their OWN iframe (n-xxx.googleusercontent.com). The page
  you visit at script.google.com is itself a wrapper around that
  inner iframe — and the wrapper's iframe doesn't always pass
  camera permission down. We can't change the GAS wrapper, but
  we CAN put OUR wrapper around the whole thing and pass camera
  permission down ourselves. Browser will respect the `allow=`
  attribute on each iframe in the chain.

  Setup steps (one-time):
    1. Deploy the standalone GAS verify portal (see README.md).
       Copy the resulting /exec URL.
    2. Replace REPLACE_WITH_GAS_DEPLOYMENT_URL below with that URL.
    3. Host this file anywhere static (Netlify Drop, GitHub Pages,
       your own web host, even a Google Drive web page).
    4. Bookmark THAT hosted URL on the Secretariat's phones — not
       the bare GAS URL.

  Day-to-day use: identical to before. Verifier visits the
  bookmarked URL, taps "Start Scanner", grants camera access ONCE
  on first visit, and scans away.
-->
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8" />
  <meta
    name="viewport"
    content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1, viewport-fit=cover"
  />
  <meta name="referrer" content="origin" />
  <meta name="theme-color" content="#0b1b3a" />
  <title>AIoTIE 2026 — Certificate Verification</title>
  <style>
    /* Full-bleed iframe — the embedded GAS portal already has its
       own padding / max-width, so this outer shell is just a
       transparent host. */
    html, body {
      margin: 0;
      padding: 0;
      height: 100%;
      width: 100%;
      background: #f6f7fb;
      overflow: hidden;
      -webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;
    }
    iframe {
      display: block;
      border: 0;
      width: 100%;
      height: 100%;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <iframe
    title="AIoTIE 2026 — Verify Portal"
    src="https://script.google.com/macros/s/AKfycbyEZNhBSBjoeHkkQapl9M6eKjSjSusM_iNbUvP0gr2UEgap90M4XV_m32zsTieaZaUIpQ/exec"
    allow="camera; microphone"
    referrerpolicy="origin"
    allowfullscreen
  ></iframe>
</body>
</html>
